7 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 49\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n|Title           = A Witch in Time\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Scott Payne\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|30|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/03/30|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Mildred and Ethel compete in the Head Girl competition Triathlon, Mildred wins chanting and flying but looses on control of her familiar Tabby. Worried her vision of Ethel making all the students disappear if she becomes head girl, Mildred uses a sandtimer to go back in time four times. Her three initial attempts all end in disaster (her dog raids the kitchen after taking the confidence potion she gave Tabby, Maud loses her voice when she yells too much in the broomstick race after the order of the competition is changed, and next time injured when Izzy comes back with her and her absence distracts Maud at a crucial moment). Fourthly, at Mr. Daisy's behest \"A great witch relies on her wits, not just her magic,\" Mildred wins the Triathlon. Meanwhile Mr Daisy's secret Patented Potions Machine is revealed and is sabotaged by Mabel, who eventually relents when Miss Hardbroom intends to sack him for incompetence.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 50\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n|Title           = Grounded\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Paul Gerstenberger\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|6|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/04/06|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = The arrival of a magical comet is announced. With Mildred and Ethel getting ready for the final head girl challenge (to create a new spell) Mildred starts to suffer from magical burnout. Knowing this Maud, Izzy and 