deleine Edmondson) and menaced by the cruel jailer Miss Splinter (played by Sue Vincent). Meanwhile Maud analyses playback and realises someone else caused Miss Cackle's demise and deliberately gets herself sent to Wormwood too with a plan to free Mildred. Ethel was doing Agatha (Ada's evil twin) Cackle's bidding and tricked Felicity into sabotaging Mildred's spell. Ethel frees Agatha. Mildred and Maud make their escape from Wormwood.\nIn a sub-plot, an attempt to comfort (the soon to be dismissed) Mr Daisy with a Happiness Potion goes wrong, when he dances in an over familiar way with Miss Hardbroom.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 52\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n|Title           = The Witching Hour: Part 2\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Neil Jones\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|20|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/04/20|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Agatha Cackle, impersonating headmistress Ada, promotes Ethel to head girl, and at the school assembly tricks everyone else into the Banishment plane of existence, including Mildred's mum (who had been messaged by Maud). Agatha locks Mr. Daisy away and thwarts Miss Hardbroom with a magic restricting broach. She also demands the Great Wizard hands over his title. Mildred's mum organises tower building with junk in the banishment plane, and they escape. \n\nMildred and Maud search for the magic reversal word (the name of Agatha Cackle's first familiar) to reverse the banishment and in the process discover Mr. Daisy locked away. He agrees to use his potion machine, so while Mildred and Maud delay Agatha with distractions, his machine's potion restores Miss Cackle. She in turn saves Mildred's Mum with the secret word. Agatha banishes herself.\n\nMildred learns Izzy Jones is her sister and Spike is her dad, who her mum (Julie) met in Morrocco just before she was born. Mildred and Ethel make peace just before Mildred is confirmed as head girl.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production and casting==\nIn November 2014, it was announced that a new series of The Worst Witch was in development with the [[British Broadcasting Corporation|BBC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a607329/the-worst-witch-writer-reveals-new-tv-adaptation-is-in-development/|title=The Worst Witch writer reveals new TV adaptation is in development|work=Digital Spy|last=Alexander|first=Susannah|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> The cast of the show was announced in October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a812479/heres-your-first-look-at-the-spooky-worst-witch-tv-remake/|title=Here's your first look at the spooky Worst Witch TV remake, featuring stars from Game of Thrones and Downton Abbey|work=Digital Spy|last=Anderton|first=Joe|date=31 October 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' actress [[Bella Ramsey]] was cast as Mildred and said filming the series \"was really good\", but there were some challenging elements and described learning the stunts as \"hard.\"<ref name=\"Bella Ramsey casting\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2016/dec/18/worst-witch-children-tv-adaptation|title=Harry Potter for girls? I\u2019m not that kind of Worst Witch, says TV\u2019s new Mildred Hubble|work=Guardian|last=Conlan|first=Tara|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Ramsey drew similarities between herself and Mildred.<ref name=\"Bella Ramsey casting\"/> Meibh Campbell played the role of Maud Spellbody for series 1, but was replaced by Megan Hughes from series 2.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/15428751.Oxfordshire_schoolgirl_set_to_become_national_star_in_new_series_of_The_Worst_Witch/|title=Oxfordshire schoolgirl Megan Hughes is set to become a national star in new series of The Worst Witch|work=Oxford Mail|last=Hughes|first=Pete|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Of her casting, Hughes said working on the show is \"great and I [Hughes] love the experience\" and that she is \"so grateful for the opportunity.\" Hughes had two auditions before being offered the part of Maud.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\"/> Hughes' mother, Claire, added that Hughes has an \"amazing time\" and is \"really happy, really positive\" throughout filming.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\"/> Tamara Smart gained the part of Enid Nightshade after four months of auditioning, which she described as \"very long\" yet \"nerve racking but at the same time very exciting.\" Smart was excited about the \"amazing experience\" when she got the part.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.borehamwoodtimes.co.uk/news/14725970.Barnet_schoolgirl_is_flying_high_at_landing_star_role_in_CBBC_show/|title=Barnet schoolgirl is flying high at landing star role in CBBC show|work=Borehamwood Times|date=6 September 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Jenny Richardson and Miriam Petche were cast as sisters Ethel and Esmerelda Hallow.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/14947530.Drama_pupil_from_Leatherhead_to_star_in_The_Worst_Witch_reboot/|title=Drama pupil from Leatherhead to star in The Worst Witch reboot|work=Your Local Guardian|last=Dickerson|first=Rachel|date=5 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://twitter.com/mark_jermin_mgt/status/733620874746732545 Mark Jermin Management on Twitter: HUGE well done to Miriam Petche who will be playing the role of Esmerelda in new CBBC remake of THE WORST WITCH!<!--Bot Generated Title-->]</ref> Tallulah Milligan, the daughter of ''[[Coronation Street]]'' and ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' actress [[Angela Griffin]], was cast as Drusilla Paddock. Griffin said Milligan \"absolutely loves\" working on the show.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jul/15/angela-griffin-shes-ace-my-mum-a-grounded-down-to-earth-yorkshirewoman|title=Angela Griffin: \u2018She\u2019s ace, my mum \u2013 a grounded, down-to-earth Yorkshirewoman\u2019|work=Guardian|last=Gray|first=Susan|date=16 July 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Dagny Rollins plays the role of Felicity Foxglove.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/showbiz-news/leanne-brown-angela-griffin-cbbc-12310052|title=Leanne Brown and Angela Griffin turn out for special CBBC Worst Witch screening|work=Manchester Evening News|date=14 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Worst Witch is filmed at [[Peckforton Castle]], [[Peckforton]] [[Cheshire]], [[England]] and [[Burg Hohenzollern]], [[Swabian Alps]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/mediapacks/worstwitch/15-facts|title=CBBC brings The Worst Witch to life for a new generation|work=BBC|date=11 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> The second series is also filmed at [[Adlington Hall]], [[Adlington, Cheshire|Adlington]], [[Cheshire]], using their grand hall, minstrel's gallery and their countryside and woods backdrop.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://marketingcheshire.co.uk/news/adlington-hall-gardens-turns-witching-academy/|title=Adlington Hall & Gardens Turns Into A Witching Academy|work=Marketing Cheshire|year=2018|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme | b09m8lyz | The Worst Witch}}\n* [https://www.netflix.com/title/80130521''The Worst Witch''] on [[Netflix]]\n* {{IMDb title|5721172|The Worst Witch}}\n\n{{The Worst Witch}}\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Worst Witch, The}}\n[[Category:BBC children's television programmes]]\n[[Category:ZDF television series]]\n[[Category:Witchcraft in television]]\n[[Category:Wizards in television]]\n[[Category:British supernatural television programmes]]\n[[Category:2017 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:The Worst Witch]]\n[[Category:Television about magic]]\n[[Category:British television programmes based on children's books]]\n[[Category:2017 German television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s German television series]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Netflix children's programming]]\n", "name_user": "QivisNeaf", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSeries 4 (2020):viewer figures 16 March", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Worst_Witch_(2017_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Enzo Lombardo", "text_new": "{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Cayarga|Fern\u00e1ndez}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Enzo Lombardo\n| image = \n| fullname = Enzo Lombardo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|4|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]], France\n| height = 1.74m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]]<br/>(on loan from [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]])\n| clubnumber = 17\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]\n| youthyears2 = 2013\u20132015 | youthclubs2 = [[AS Saint-Priest|Saint-Priest]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs1 = [[AS Saint-Priest|Saint-Priest]] | caps1 = 22 | goals1 = 5\n| years2 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs2 = [[RCD Mallorca B|Mallorca B]] | caps2 = 43 | goals2 = 7\n| years3 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[UD Poblense|Poblense]] (loan) | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2018\u2013 | clubs4 = [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] | caps4 = 1 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2018\u2013 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]] (loan) | caps5 = 51 | goals5 = 6\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 8 December 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Enzo Lombardo''' (born 16 April 1997) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for Spanish club [[Racing de Santander]], on loan from [[RCD Mallorca]].\n\n==Club career==\nLombardo was born in [[D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]], and began his career with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]. Released at the age of 16, he subsequently joined [[AS Saint-Priest]], and made his senior debut with the [[Championnat de France Amateur]] club in the [[2015\u201316 Championnat de France Amateur|2015\u201316 season]].\n\nOn 28 June 2016, Lombardo joined [[RCD Mallorca]] and was initially assigned to [[RCD Mallorca B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/ol-mercato-enzo-lombardo-ex-ol-quitte-saint-priest-pour-majorque,122333.html|title=OL \u2013 Mercato: Enzo Lombardo (ex-OL) quitte Saint-Priest pour Majorque|trans-title=OL \u2013 Transfer market: Enzo Lombardo (formerly of OL) leaves Saint-Priest for Mallorca|publisher=Olympique-et-Lyonnais|language=fr|date=28 June 2016|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref> The following 31 January, however, he was loaned to [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[UD Poblense]] until June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdmallorca.es/contenidos/noticias/noticia/nadal-lima-y-enzo-lombardo-cedidos-al-ud-poblense|title=Nadal, Lima y Enzo Lombardo cedidos al UD Poblense|trans-title=Nadal, Lima and Enzo Lombardo loaned to UD Poblense|publisher=RCD Mallorca|language=es|date=31 January 2017|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2018, after being a regular starter with Mallorca B, Lombardo was loaned to third division side [[Racing de Santander]] for [[2018\u201319 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticia/enzo-lombardo-quinto-refuerzo-del-racing-201819|title=Enzo Lombardo, quinto refuerzo del Racing 2018/19|trans-title=Enzo Lombardo, fifth addition of Racing 2018/19|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=9 July 2018|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref> On 9 August of the following year, after achieving promotion to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]], his loan was renewed for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticia/enzo-lombardo-noveno-refuerzo-del-racing-201920|title=Enzo Lombardo, noveno refuerzo del Racing 2019/20|trans-title=Enzo Lombardo, ninth addition of Racing 2019/20|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=9 August 2019|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nLombardo made his professional debut on 17 August 2019, starting in a 0\u20131 home loss against [[M\u00e1laga CF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2019/08/17/5d5844f2ca474107698b457e.html|title=El M\u00e1laga se sobrepone a las bajas y amarga el regreso del Racing|trans-title=M\u00e1laga overcome the absences and bitter Racing's return|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=17 August 2019|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|23346}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|281681<!-- -enzo-lombardo -->}}\n*{{LaPreferente|210555/enzo-lombardo}}\n*{{Soccerway|enzo-lombardo/418975}}\n\n{{Racing de Santander squad}}\n<!--{{RCD Mallorca squad}}-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lombardo, Enzo}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Championnat National 2 players]]\n[[Category:AS Saint-Priest players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:RCD Mallorca B players]]\n[[Category:RCD Mallorca players]]\n[[Category:Racing de Santander players]]\n[[Category:French expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Cayarga|Fern\u00e1ndez}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Enzo Lombardo\n| image =\n| fullname = Enzo Lombardo\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|4|16|df=y}} \n| birth_place = [[D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]], France\n| height = 1.74m\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]]<br/>(on loan from [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]])\n| clubnumber = 17\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]\n| youthyears2 = 2013\u20132015 | youthclubs2 = [[AS Saint-Priest|Saint-Priest]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs1 = [[AS Saint-Priest|Saint-Priest]] | caps1 = 22 | goals1 = 5\n| years2 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs2 = [[RCD Mallorca B|Mallorca B]] | caps2 = 43 | goals2 = 7\n| years3 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[UD Poblense|Poblense]] (loan) | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2018\u2013 | clubs4 = [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] | caps4 = 1 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2018\u2013 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]] (loan) | caps5 = 51 | goals5 = 6\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 8 December 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Enzo Lombardo''' (born 16 April 1997) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for Spanish club [[Racing de Santander]], on loan from [[RCD Mallorca]].\n\n==Club career==\nLombardo was born in [[D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]], and began his career with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]. Released at the age of 16, he subsequently joined [[AS Saint-Priest]], and made his senior debut with the [[Championnat de France Amateur]] club in the [[2015\u201316 Championnat de France Amateur|2015\u201316 season]].\n\nOn 28 June 2016, Lombardo joined [[RCD Mallorca]] and was initially assigned to [[RCD Mallorca B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/ol-mercato-enzo-lombardo-ex-ol-quitte-saint-priest-pour-majorque,122333.html|title=OL \u2013 Mercato: Enzo Lombardo (ex-OL) quitte Saint-Priest pour Majorque|trans-title=OL \u2013 Transfer market: Enzo Lombardo (formerly of OL) leaves Saint-Priest for Mallorca|publisher=Olympique-et-Lyonnais|language=fr|date=28 June 2016|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref> The following 31 January, however, he was loaned to [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[UD Poblense]] until June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdmallorca.es/contenidos/noticias/noticia/nadal-lima-y-enzo-lombardo-cedidos-al-ud-poblense|title=Nadal, Lima y Enzo Lombardo cedidos al UD Poblense|trans-title=Nadal, Lima and Enzo Lombardo loaned to UD Poblense|publisher=RCD Mallorca|language=es|date=31 January 2017|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2018, after being a regular starter with Mallorca B, Lombardo was loaned to third division side [[Racing de Santander]] for [[2018\u201319 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|the campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticia/enzo-lombardo-quinto-refuerzo-del-racing-201819|title=Enzo Lombardo, quinto refuerzo del Racing 2018/19|trans-title=Enzo Lombardo, fifth addition of Racing 2018/19|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=9 July 2018|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref> On 9 August of the following year, after achieving promotion to [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]], his loan was renewed for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticia/enzo-lombardo-noveno-refuerzo-del-racing-201920|title=Enzo Lombardo, noveno refuerzo del Racing 2019/20|trans-title=Enzo Lombardo, ninth addition of Racing 2019/20|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=9 August 2019|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nLombardo made his professional debut on 17 August 2019, starting in a 0\u20131 home loss against [[M\u00e1laga CF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/cronica/2019/08/17/5d5844f2ca474107698b457e.html|title=El M\u00e1laga se sobrepone a las bajas y amarga el regreso del Racing|trans-title=M\u00e1laga overcome the absences and bitter Racing's return|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=17 August 2019|accessdate=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|23346}}\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|281681-enzo-lombardo}}\n*{{LaPreferente|210555/enzo-lombardo}}\n*{{Soccerway|enzo-lombardo/418975}}\n\n{{Racing de Santander squad}}\n<!--{{RCD Mallorca squad}}-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lombardo, Enzo}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from D\u00e9cines-Charpieu]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Championnat National 2 players]]\n[[Category:AS Saint-Priest p