\u20131861}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Edward Clark (governor)|Edward Clark]]}}\n{{S-par|us-sen}}\n{{U.S. Senator box|state=Texas|class=2|before=None|after=[[John Hemphill (politician)|John Hemphill]]|alongside=[[Thomas Jefferson Rusk|Thomas J. Rusk]], [[James Pinckney Henderson|J. Pinckney Henderson]] and [[Matthias Ward]]\n|years=February 21, 1846 \u2013 March 3, 1859}}\n{{S-end}}}}\n{{USSenTX}}\n{{Governors of Tennessee}}\n{{TXPresidents}}\n{{Governors of Texas}}\n{{Republic of Texas}}\n{{United States presidential election, 1860}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Houston, Sam}}\n\n[[Category:Sam Houston| ]]\n[[Category:1793 births]]\n[[Category:1863 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:American emigrants to Mexico]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scotch-Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American army personnel of the War of 1812]]\n[[Category:American prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Army of the Republic of Texas generals]]\n[[Category:Confederate state governors]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party United States senators]]\n[[Category:Democratic-Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Democratic-Republican Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Governors of Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Governors of Texas]]\n[[Category:Independent state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Jacksonian members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Know-Nothing United States senators]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:People from Maryville, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:People from Rockbridge County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:People of Texas in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category:People of the Creek War]]\n[[Category:People of the Texas Revolution]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Republic of Texas]]\n[[Category:American slave owners]]\n[[Category:Southern Unionists in the American Civil War]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Democratic-Republicans]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Jacksonians]]\n[[Category:Tennessee lawyers]]\n[[Category:Baptists from Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas Consultation delegates]]\n[[Category:Texas Democrats]]\n[[Category:Texas Independents]]\n[[Category:Texas Know Nothings]]\n[[Category:United States Army officers]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1860 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:United States senators from Texas]]\n[[Category:People from Huntsville, Texas]]\n[[Category:People from San Augustine, Texas]]\n[[Category:Signers of the Texas Declaration of Independence]]\n[[Category:Baptists from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Baptists from Virginia]]\n[[Category:Converts to Baptist denominations from Roman Catholicism]]\n", "name_user": "Bdmcpeek", "label": "safe", "comment": "This article listed the date that Texas officially became a US state was in February 1846.  This is not true.  Texas officially became a US state on December 29, 1845.  February 19, 1846, was the date the transfer of government was complete.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Houston"}
{"title_page": "Jawed Karim", "text_new": "{{Short description|Co-founder of YouTube}}\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jawed Karim\n| image              = Jawed Karim 2008.jpg\n| caption            = Jawed Karim in August 2008\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1979|10|28}}\n| birth_place        = [[Merseburg]], [[East Germany]] (present-day [[Germany]])\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[Americans|American]]/[[Germans|German]]\n| known_for          = Co-founder of [[YouTube]]<br/>Uploader of the [[Me at the zoo|first video ever]] on YouTube\n| alma mater         = [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]] ([[Bachelor of Science|BS]])<br>[[Stanford University]] ([[Master of Science|MS]])\n| occupation         = \n| module             = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| name            = jawed\n| channel_name    = jawed\n| years_active    = 2005\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Wildlife]]\n}}\n| subscribers     = ~785,000\n| views           = ~90 million\n| network         = \n| associated_acts = \n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2015\n| stats_update    = 22 February 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Jawed Karim''' ({{lang-bn|\u099c\u09be\u09ad\u09c7\u09a6 \u0995\u09b0\u09bf\u09ae}}; born 28 October 1979) is an American computer scientist and [[Internet entrepreneur]] of [[Bangladeshi Americans|Bangladeshi]]-[[German Americans|German]] descent. He is the co-founder of [[YouTube]] and the first person to upload a video to the site. This inaugural video, titled ''[[Me at the zoo]]'' uploaded on 23 April 2005, has been viewed about 90{{nbsp}}million times {{as of|2020|4|lc=y}}. During Karim's time working at [[PayPal]], where he met the fellow YouTube co-founders [[Steve Chen|Steven Chen]] and [[Chad Hurley]], he had designed many of the core components including its real-time anti-[[Internet fraud|Internet-fraud]] system.\n\n==Personal life==\nKarim was born on 28 October 1979 in [[Merseburg]], [[East Germany]], to a [[Germans|German]] mother and [[Bangladeshis|Bangladeshi]] father. He was the elder of two boys.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/2006-10-11-youtube-karim_x.htm |title=Surprise! There's a third YouTube co-founder |accessdate=22 July 2017 |work=USA Today}}</ref> He crossed the [[inner German border]] with his family in the early 1980s because of [[xenophobia]],<ref name=\"diewelt\">{{cite news |last=Keese |first=Christoph |date=22 October 2006 |title=Sergey Brin und Jawed Karim \u2013 zwei Karierren |url=https://www.welt.de/print-welt/article89110/Sergey-Brin-und-Jawed-Karim-zwei-Karierren.html |newspaper=[[Die Welt]] |language=de |accessdate=20 August 2017 |quote=Der andere hei\u00dft Jawed Karim und wurde 1979 in Merseburg/DDR geboren. Sein Vater kam aus Bangladesch, seine Mutter aus dem Harz. Die Karims waren als Ausl\u00e4nder verp\u00f6nt und wanderten deswegen 1982 in den Westen aus. In Neuss schlug ihnen wieder Fremdenhass entgegen; deshalb zogen sie in die USA}}</ref> growing up in [[Neuss]], [[West Germany]].{{refn|group=note|Sources vary regarding the year that the family moved from East Germany to West Germany. ''The New York Times'' says 1980.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> ''[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|Star Weekend Magazine]]'' says at the end of summer 1981.<ref name=\"swm8Dec2006\">{{cite news |last=Rahman |first=Muhit |date=8 December 2006 |title=The Greatest Possibilities: The Jawed Karim Story |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/magazine/2006/12/02/sfeature.htm |work=Star Weekend Magazine |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> ''[[Die Welt]]'' says 1982.<ref name=\"diewelt\" />}} Experiencing xenophobia there as well,<ref name=\"diewelt\" /> Karim moved with his family to [[Saint Paul, Minnesota]], in 1992.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> He graduated from [[Saint Paul Central High School]]<ref name=\"swm8Dec2006\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Christensen |first=Tesha M. |date=5 September 2016 |title=Year-long events mark Central High School 150th anniversary |url=http://www.monitorsaintpaul.com/year-long-events-mark-central-high-school-150th-anniversary/ |newspaper=Monitor St. Paul |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> and later attended the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]. He left campus prior to graduating to become an early employee at [[PayPal]], but continued his coursework,<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> earning his bachelor's degree in computer science.<ref>{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=YouTube co-founder to be commencement speaker at Illinois |url=https://news.illinois.edu/blog/view/6367/206692 |publisher=University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign |date=27 March 2007 |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> He subsequently earned a master's degree in computer science from [[Stanford University]].<ref>{{cite news |date=January 2007 |title=Planet Cardinal |url=https://alumni-gsb.stanford.edu/get/page/magazine/article/?article_id=32549 |newspaper=Stanford Magazine}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jawed Karim 2004.jpg|left|thumb|200px|Karim in September 2004]]\n\n==Career==\nIn 1998, Karim served an Internship at [[Silicon Graphics]], Inc. where he worked on 3D voxel data management for very large data sets for [[volume rendering]], including the data for the [[Visible Human Project]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Speakers, Graphics Conference|url=https://www-s.acm.illinois.edu/conference/1998/jawed_k.html|access-date=24 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919130455/https://www-s.acm.illinois.edu/conference/1998/jawed_k.html|archive-date=19 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> While working at PayPal, he met [[Chad Hurley]] and [[Steve Chen (YouTube)|Steve Chen]]. Three years later, in 2005, they founded the YouTube video sharing website.<ref name=\"usatoday-nov-21-2005\">[https://www.usatoday.com/tech/news/techinnovations/2005-11-21-video-websites_x.htm Video websites pop up, invite postings], ''USA Today'', 21 November 2005</ref> YouTube's first ever video, ''[[Me at the zoo]]'', was uploaded by Karim on 23 April 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jNQXAC9IVRw |title=Me at the zoo, YouTube's first ever video |last1=Karim |first1=Jawed |date=23 April 2005}}</ref>\n\nAfter co-founding the company and developing the YouTube concept and website with Chad Hurley and Steve Chen, Karim enrolled as a graduate student in computer science at Stanford University while acting as an adviser to YouTube. When the site was introduced in February 2005, Karim agreed not to be an employee and simply be an informal adviser, and that he was focusing on his studies.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/12/technology/12tube.html?hp&ex=1160712000&en=c6ddbc2fdb0a4dea&ei=5094 |title=With YouTube, Student Hits Jackpot Again |last=Helft |first=Miguel |date=12 October 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> As a result, he took a much lower share in the company compared to Hurley and Chen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.siliconvalleywatcher.com/mt/archives/2006/10/jawed_who_meet.php |title=Jawed Who? Meet YouTube's silent partner |website=Silicon Valley Watcher}}</ref> Because of his smaller role in the company, Karim was mostly unknown to the public as the third founder until YouTube was acquired by Google in 2006. Despite his lower share in the company, the purchase was still large enough that he received 137,443 shares of stock, worth about $64&nbsp;million based on Google's closing stock price at the time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/07/technology/07cnd-google.html?ex=1328504400&en=96fcc0326d0a7ef6&ei=5088 |title=YouTube's Payoff: Hundreds of Millions for the Founders |last=Helft |first=Miguel |date=7 February 2007 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2006, Karim gave a lecture about the history of YouTube at the [[University of Illinois]] annual ACM Conference entitled ''YouTube From Concept to Hyper growth''. Karim returned again to the University of Illinois in May 2007 as the 136th and youngest Commencement Speaker in the school's history.<ref>[http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/about/dwelcome.php Welcome to Engineering at Illinois] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513191504/http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/about/dwelcome.php |date=13 May 2008 }}, University of Illinois</ref><ref>[http://www.cs.uiuc.edu/mm/videos/articles/Karim2007commencement.html 136th Commencement Address] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411223550/http://www.cs.uiuc.edu/mm/videos/articles/Karim2007commencement.html |date=11 April 2009 }}, University of Illinois, 13 May 2007.</ref>\n\n==Investments==\nIn March 2008, Karim launched a venture fund called Youniversity Ventures with partners [[Keith Rabois]] and [[Kevin Hartz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=YouTube Co-Founder Starts Venture Capital Firm |url=http://mashable.com/2008/03/20/youniversity-ventures/ |publisher=[[Mashable]] |date=20 March 2008}}</ref> Karim is one of [[Airbnb]]'s first investors, investing in the company's initial [[Seed money|seed round]] in April 2009.<ref name=\"Gallagher2017\">{{cite book|last=Gallagher|first=Leigh|url=https://books.google.com/?id=4iGtDQAAQBAJ&dq=airbnb+story&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=jawed%20karim&f=false|title=The Airbnb Story: How Three Ordinary Guys Disrupted an Industry, Made Billions. and Created Plenty of Controversy|date=14 February 2017|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|year=|isbn=978-0-544-95387-1|location=|page=31|pages=|chapter=The Hustle|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Response to Google+ integration with YouTube==\nOn 6 November 2013, YouTube began requiring that commenting on its videos be done via a [[Google+]] account, a move that was widely opposed by the YouTube community. An online petition to revert the change garnered over 240,000 signatures.<ref>{{cite news |title=YouTube faces backlash for Google+ integration |publisher=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/11/08/tech/social-media/youtube-comment-backlash/ |accessdate=10 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn response to Google requiring YouTube members to use Google+ for its comment system, Karim wrote on his YouTube account, \"why the fuck do i need a Google+ account to comment on a video\", and updated the video description on his first video titled [[Me at the zoo]] to ''I can't comment here anymore, since i don't want a Google+ account''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cheredar|first=Tom|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/11/08/youtube-cofounders-first-public-comment-in-8-years-why-the-f-do-i-need-a-google-account-to-comment-on-a-video/|title=YouTube cofounder's first public comment in 8 years: why the f*** [sic] do i need a Google+ account to comment on a video? <!-- bowdlerization is in VentureBeat text, but not in their screenshot of Karim's comment -->|date=8 November 2013|work=VentureBeat|accessdate=11 November 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn response to pressure from the YouTube community, Google publicly apologized for forcing Google+ users to use their real names, which was one of the reasons the Google+ integration was unpopular with YouTube users.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Google Plus Finally Gives Up on Its Ineffective, Dangerous Real-Name Policy |work=Slate |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/future_tense/2014/07/17/google_plus_finally_ditches_its_ineffective_dangerous_real_name_policy.html |accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> Google subsequently dropped its Google+ requirement across all products, beginning with YouTube.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/07/27/google-is-dropping-its-google-requirement-across-all-products-starting-with-youtube/ |title=Google is dropping its Google+ requirement across all products, starting with YouTube |work=VentureBeat |accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref> Google announced in October 2018 its intention to permanently shut down Google+ as it had failed to achieve broad consumer or developer adoption.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/10/08/tech/google-plus-security/index.html |title=Google+ to shut down |publisher=CNN |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/project-strobe/ |title=Project Strobe: Protecting your data, improving our third-party APIs, and sunsetting consumer Google+ |publisher=Google |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> Google+ was closed for personal accounts on 2 April 2019.\n\n==Publications==\nKarim has published articles on programming in ''[[Dr. Dobb's Journal]]'', including one on loading rendering and animating Quake models.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dr. Dobbs Article, A Windows 3D Model Viewer for OpenGL |url=http://www.drdobbs.com/windows/a-windows-3d-model-viewerfor-opengl/184410607}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PayPal Mafia]]\n* [[Fazlur Rahman Khan]]\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* [[Me at the zoo]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.jawed.com/ Jawed Karim's Personal Website]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/jawed Jawed's YouTube Profile]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080508185217/https://www.youtube.com/user/jawed Cache of Jawed's YouTube Profile in 2008]\n* [http://www.yventures.com/ Youniversity Ventures]\n*''[https://web.archive.org/web/20090828032440/http://www.news-gazette.com/news/opinions/editorials/2006/10/16/he_went_off_to_college_to_make_his He went off to college to make his fortune]'' \u2013 The News-Gazette (16 October 2006)\n\n{{You Tube}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karim, Jawed}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century American scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century German businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century German scientists]]\n[[Category:American computer businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American computer programmers]]\n[[Category:American computer scientists]]\n[[Category:American people of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:American technology chief executives]]\n[[Category:American technology company founders]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi computer programmers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Saint Paul, Minnesota]]\n[[Category:American businessmen of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:East German emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:East German emigrants to West Germany]]\n[[Category:East German scientists]]\n[[Category:German computer programmers]]\n[[Category:German computer scientists]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:German people of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:German YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet pioneers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:PayPal people]]\n[[Category:People from Merseburg]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign alumni]]\n[[Category:West German emigrants]]\n[[Category:YouTube]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2005]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Co-founder of YouTube}}\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Jawed Karim\n| image           = Jawed Karim 2008.jpg\n| caption         = Jawed Karim in August 2008\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1979|10|28}}\n| birth_place     = [[Merseburg]], [[East Germany]] (present-day [[Germany]])\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| nationality     = [[Americans|American]]/[[Germans|German]]\n| known_for       = Co-founder of [[YouTube]]<br/>Uploader of the [[Me at the zoo|first video ever]] on YouTube\n| alma mater      = [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]] ([[Bachelor of Science|BS]])<br>[[Stanford University]] ([[Master of Science|MS]])\n| occupation      = \n| module          = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| name            = jawed\n| channel_name    = jawed\n| years_active    = 2005\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Wildlife]]\n}}\n| subscribers     = ~785,000\n| views           = ~89 million\n| network         = \n| associated_acts = \n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2015\n| stats_update    = 22 February 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Jawed Karim''' ({{lang-bn|\u099c\u09be\u09ad\u09c7\u09a6 \u0995\u09b0\u09bf\u09ae}}; born 28 October 1979) is an American computer scientist and [[Internet entrepreneur]] of [[Bangladeshi Americans|Bangladeshi]]-[[German Americans|German]] descent. He is the co-founder of [[YouTube]] and the first person to upload a video to the site. This inaugural video, titled ''[[Me at the zoo]]'' uploaded on 23 April 2005, has been viewed about 90{{nbsp}}million times {{as of|2020|4|lc=y}}. During Karim's time working at [[PayPal]], where he met the fellow YouTube co-founders [[Steve Chen|Steven Chen]] and [[Chad Hurley]], he had designed many of the core components including its real-time anti-[[Internet fraud|Internet-fraud]] system.\n\n==Personal life==\nKarim was born on 28 October 1979 in [[Merseburg]], [[East Germany]], to a [[Germans|German]] mother and [[Bangladeshis|Bangladeshi]] father. He was the elder of two boys.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/2006-10-11-youtube-karim_x.htm |title=Surprise! There's a third YouTube co-founder |accessdate=22 July 2017 |work=USA Today}}</ref> He crossed the [[inner German border]] with his family in the early 1980s because of [[xenophobia]],<ref name=\"diewelt\">{{cite news |last=Keese |first=Christoph |date=22 October 2006 |title=Sergey Brin und Jawed Karim \u2013 zwei Karierren |url=https://www.welt.de/print-welt/article89110/Sergey-Brin-und-Jawed-Karim-zwei-Karierren.html |newspaper=[[Die Welt]] |language=de |accessdate=20 August 2017 |quote=Der andere hei\u00dft Jawed Karim und wurde 1979 in Merseburg/DDR geboren. Sein Vater kam aus Bangladesch, seine Mutter aus dem Harz. Die Karims waren als Ausl\u00e4nder verp\u00f6nt und wanderten deswegen 1982 in den Westen aus. In Neuss schlug ihnen wieder Fremdenhass entgegen; deshalb zogen sie in die USA}}</ref> growing up in [[Neuss]], [[West Germany]].{{refn|group=note|Sources vary regarding the year that the family moved from East Germany to West Germany. ''The New York Times'' says 1980.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> ''[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|Star Weekend Magazine]]'' says at the end of summer 1981.<ref name=\"swm8Dec2006\">{{cite news |last=Rahman |first=Muhit |date=8 December 2006 |title=The Greatest Possibilities: The Jawed Karim Story |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/magazine/2006/12/02/sfeature.htm |work=Star Weekend Magazine |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> ''[[Die Welt]]'' says 1982.<ref name=\"diewelt\" />}} Experiencing xenophobia there as well,<ref name=\"diewelt\" /> Karim moved with his family to [[Saint Paul, Minnesota]], in 1992.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> He graduated from [[Saint Paul Central High School]]<ref name=\"swm8Dec2006\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Christensen |first=Tesha M. |date=5 September 2016 |title=Year-long events mark Central High School 150th anniversary |url=http://www.monitorsaintpaul.com/year-long-events-mark-central-high-school-150th-anniversary/ |newspaper=Monitor St. Paul |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> and later attended the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]. He left campus prior to graduating to become an early employee at [[PayPal]], but continued his coursework,<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\" /> earning his bachelor's degree in computer science.<ref>{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=YouTube co-founder to be commencement speaker at Illinois |url=https://news.illinois.edu/blog/view/6367/206692 |publisher=University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign |date=27 March 2007 |accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> He subsequently earned a master's degree in computer science from [[Stanford University]].<ref>{{cite news |date=January 2007 |title=Planet Cardinal |url=https://alumni-gsb.stanford.edu/get/page/magazine/article/?article_id=32549 |newspaper=Stanford Magazine}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jawed Karim 2004.jpg|left|thumb|200px|Karim in September 2004]]\n\n==Career==\nIn 1998, Karim served an Internship at [[Silicon Graphics]], Inc. where he worked on 3D voxel data management for very large data sets for [[volume rendering]], including the data for the [[Visible Human Project]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Speakers, Graphics Conference|url=https://www-s.acm.illinois.edu/conference/1998/jawed_k.html|access-date=24 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919130455/https://www-s.acm.illinois.edu/conference/1998/jawed_k.html|archive-date=19 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> While working at PayPal, he met [[Chad Hurley]] and [[Steve Chen (YouTube)|Steve Chen]]. Three years later, in 2005, they founded the YouTube video sharing website.<ref name=\"usatoday-nov-21-2005\">[https://www.usatoday.com/tech/news/techinnovations/2005-11-21-video-websites_x.htm Video websites pop up, invite postings], ''USA Today'', 21 November 2005</ref> YouTube's first ever video, ''[[Me at the zoo]]'', was uploaded by Karim on 23 April 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jNQXAC9IVRw |title=Me at the zoo, YouTube's first ever video |last1=Karim |first1=Jawed |date=23 April 2005}}</ref>\n\nAfter co-founding the company and developing the YouTube concept and website with Chad Hurley and Steve Chen, Karim enrolled as a graduate student in computer science at Stanford University while acting as an adviser to YouTube. When the site was introduced in February 2005, Karim agreed not to be an employee and simply be an informal adviser, and that he was focusing on his studies.<ref name=\"Student Hits Jackpot Again\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/12/technology/12tube.html?hp&ex=1160712000&en=c6ddbc2fdb0a4dea&ei=5094 |title=With YouTube, Student Hits Jackpot Again |last=Helft |first=Miguel |date=12 October 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> As a result, he took a much lower share in the company compared to Hurley and Chen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.siliconvalleywatcher.com/mt/archives/2006/10/jawed_who_meet.php |title=Jawed Who? Meet YouTube's silent partner |website=Silicon Valley Watcher}}</ref> Because of his smaller role in the company, Karim was mostly unknown to the public as the third founder until YouTube was acquired by Google in 2006. Despite his lower share in the company, the purchase was still large enough that he received 137,443 shares of stock, worth about $64&nbsp;million based on Google's closing stock price at the time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/07/technology/07cnd-google.html?ex=1328504400&en=96fcc0326d0a7ef6&ei=5088 |title=YouTube's Payoff: Hundreds of Millions for the Founders |last=Helft |first=Miguel |date=7 February 2007 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2006, Karim gave a lecture about the history of YouTube at the [[University of Illinois]] annual ACM Conference entitled ''YouTube From Concept to Hyper growth''. Karim returned again to the University of Illinois in May 2007 as the 136th and youngest Commencement Speaker in the school's history.<ref>[http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/about/dwelcome.php Welcome to Engineering at Illinois] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513191504/http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/about/dwelcome.php |date=13 May 2008 }}, University of Illinois</ref><ref>[http://www.cs.uiuc.edu/mm/videos/articles/Karim2007commencement.html 136th Commencement Address] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411223550/http://www.cs.uiuc.edu/mm/videos/articles/Karim2007commencement.html |date=11 April 2009 }}, University of Illinois, 13 May 2007.</ref>\n\n==Investments==\nIn March 2008, Karim launched a venture fund called Youniversity Ventures with partners [[Keith Rabois]] and [[Kevin Hartz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=YouTube Co-Founder Starts Venture Capital Firm |url=http://mashable.com/2008/03/20/youniversity-ventures/ |publisher=[[Mashable]] |date=20 March 2008}}</ref> Karim is one of [[Airbnb]]'s first investors, investing in the company's initial [[Seed money|seed round]] in April 2009.<ref name=\"Gallagher2017\">{{cite book|last=Gallagher|first=Leigh|url=https://books.google.com/?id=4iGtDQAAQBAJ&dq=airbnb+story&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=jawed%20karim&f=false|title=The Airbnb Story: How Three Ordinary Guys Disrupted an Industry, Made Billions. and Created Plenty of Controversy|date=14 February 2017|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|year=|isbn=978-0-544-95387-1|location=|page=31|pages=|chapter=The Hustle|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Response to Google+ integration with YouTube==\nOn 6 November 2013, YouTube began requiring that commenting on its videos be done via a [[Google+]] account, a move that was widely opposed by the YouTube community. An online petition to revert the change garnered over 240,000 signatures.<ref>{{cite news |title=YouTube faces backlash for Google+ integration |publisher=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/11/08/tech/social-media/youtube-comment-backlash/ |accessdate=10 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn response to Google requiring YouTube members to use Google+ for its comment system, Karim wrote on his YouTube account, \"why the fuck do i need a Google+ account to comment on a video\", and updated the video description on his first video titled [[Me at the zoo]] to ''I can't comment here anymore, since i don't want a Google+ account''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cheredar|first=Tom|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/11/08/youtube-cofounders-first-public-comment-in-8-years-why-the-f-do-i-need-a-google-account-to-comment-on-a-video/|title=YouTube cofounder's first public comment in 8 years: why the f*** [sic] do i need a Google+ account to comment on a video? <!-- bowdlerization is in VentureBeat text, but not in their screenshot of Karim's comment -->|date=8 November 2013|work=VentureBeat|accessdate=11 November 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn response to pressure from the YouTube community, Google publicly apologized for forcing Google+ users to use their real names, which was one of the reasons the Google+ integration was unpopular with YouTube users.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Google Plus Finally Gives Up on Its Ineffective, Dangerous Real-Name Policy |work=Slate |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/future_tense/2014/07/17/google_plus_finally_ditches_its_ineffective_dangerous_real_name_policy.html |accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref> Google subsequently dropped its Google+ requirement across all products, beginning with YouTube.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/07/27/google-is-dropping-its-google-requirement-across-all-products-starting-with-youtube/ |title=Google is dropping its Google+ requirement across all products, starting with YouTube |work=VentureBeat |accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref> Google announced in October 2018 its intention to permanently shut down Google+ as it had failed to achieve broad consumer or developer adoption.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/10/08/tech/google-plus-security/index.html |title=Google+ to shut down |publisher=CNN |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/project-strobe/ |title=Project Strobe: Protecting your data, improving our third-party APIs, and sunsetting consumer Google+ |publisher=Google |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> Google+ was closed for personal accounts on 2 April 2019.\n\n==Publications==\nKarim has published articles on programming in ''[[Dr. Dobb's Journal]]'', including one on loading rendering and animating Quake models.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dr. Dobbs Article, A Windows 3D Model Viewer for OpenGL |url=http://www.drdobbs.com/windows/a-windows-3d-model-viewerfor-opengl/184410607}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PayPal Mafia]]\n* [[Fazlur Rahman Khan]]\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* [[Me at the zoo]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.jawed.com/ Jawed Karim's Personal Website]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/jawed Jawed's YouTube Profile]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080508185217/https://www.youtube.com/user/jawed Cache of Jawed's YouTube Profile in 2008]\n* [http://www.yventures.com/ Youniversity Ventures]\n*''[https://web.archive.org/web/20090828032440/http://www.news-gazette.com/news/opinions/editorials/2006/10/16/he_went_off_to_college_to_make_his He went off to college to make his fortune]'' \u2013 The News-Gazette (16 October 2006)\n\n{{You Tube}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karim, Jawed}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century American scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century German businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century German scientists]]\n[[Category:American computer businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American computer programmers]]\n[[Category:American computer scientists]]\n[[Category:American people of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:American technology chief executives]]\n[[Category:American technology company founders]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi computer programmers]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Saint Paul, Minnesota]]\n[[Category:American businessmen of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:East German emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:East German emigrants to West Germany]]\n[[Category:East German scientists]]\n[[Category:German computer programmers]]\n[[Category:German computer scientists]]\n[[Category:German emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:German people of Bangladeshi descent]]\n[[Category:German YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet pioneers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:PayPal people]]\n[[Category:People from Merseburg]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign alumni]]\n[[Category:West German emigrants]]\n[[Category:YouTube]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2005]]\n", "name_user": "Kiryllp", "label": "safe", "comment": "Viewcount changed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jawed_Karim"}
{"title_page": "Sir (singer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = SiR\n| image            = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| alias            = \n| birth_name       = Sir Darryl Farris\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1986|11|05}}\n| birth_place      = [[Inglewood, California]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Soul music|soul]]}}\n| instrument       = [[Singing|Vocals]]\n| occupation       = {{hlist|[[Singing|Singer]]|[[songwriter]]|[[record producer]]}}\n| years_active     = 2012\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Top Dawg Entertainment|Top Dawg]]|[[RCA Records|RCA]]|Fresh Selects (former)}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Kendrick Lamar]]|[[Anderson Paak]]|[[Jay Rock]]|[[Isaiah Rashad]]|[[Big K.R.I.T.]]|[[EarthGang]]|[[Schoolboy Q]]}}\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Sir Darryl Farris''' (born November 5, 1986), known mononymously as '''Sir''' (stylized as '''SiR'''), is an American [[Singing|singer]], [[songwriter]] and [[record producer]] from [[Inglewood, California]]. He is signed to [[Top Dawg Entertainment]] and released his debut album on the label titled ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]'' on January 19, 2018. \n\n==Early life==\nSir Darryl Farris grew up in a musical family with his mother, brothers, and cousin being gospel singers in Inglewood. He earned a degree in recording arts at the [[Los Angeles Film School|Los Angeles Film School ]] and developed his songwriting, arranging, and production skills. His mother was a backup singer for [[Michael Jackson]] and [[Anita Baker]], and his uncle [[Andrew Gouche]] was a bassist for [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], and he is the younger brother of rapper [[D Smoke]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/sir-mn0003419699/biography|title=SiR - Biography & History - AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"LAWeekly\">{{cite web |title=R&B SINGER-SONGWRITER SIR IS PROUD TO REP INGLEWOOD'S THRIVING MUSIC SCENE |url=https://www.laweekly.com/rb-singer-songwriter-sir-is-proud-to-rep-inglewoods-thriving-music-scene/ |website=LA Weekly |accessdate=4 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\n===2007\u20142014: Career beginnings===\nIn 2007, SiR joined a songwriting group called WoodWorks with his brothers and his cousin [[Tiffany Gouch\u00e9]], who wrote songs for [[Jaheim]] and [[The Pussycat Dolls]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Interview: Jill Scott, Tyrese and Bilal songwriter SiR |url=https://www.factmag.com/2015/08/02/sir-interview/ |website=Fact Mag |accessdate=4 November 2019}}</ref> He landed a job engineering for [[Tyrese Gibson]] in 2012 while quietly developing his craft as a songwriter. After meeting the songwriting duo [[Dre & Vidal]], he went on to work with [[Anita Baker]] and, from 2011 through 2015, co-wrote material for the likes of [[Ginuwine]], [[Jill Scott]], and [[Stevie Wonder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2017-01-23-sir-signs-to-tde|title=An Introduction to SiR, TDE\u2019s Soulful New Signing|website=Djbooth.net|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> In 2014, he featured on [[Anderson .Paak]]'s album ''[[Venice (Anderson Paak album)|Venice]]''.\n\n===2015\u20142018: Signing to Top Dawg Entertainment and ''November''===\nOn July 31, 2015, SiR released his first independent album titled ''Seven Sundays'', which got the attention of [[Dave Free]]. He was later featured on [[Jay Rock]]'s ''[[90059]]'' on the song \"The Ways\", and [[Isaiah Rashad]]'s ''[[The Sun's Tirade]]'' on the song \"Rope / Rosegold\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Yoh|title=TDE Reveals Lance SkiiiWalker is Their \"John Doe\" New Artist - DJBooth Article|url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2016-05-11-lance-skiiiwalker-tde-new-artist|website=DJBooth.net|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2016/08/30/isaiah-rashad-the-suns-tirade-tracklisting/ |title=Isaiah Rashad Taps Kendrick Lamar, Jay Rock for 'The Sun's Tirade' |work=[[Rap-Up]] |date=August 30, 2016 |accessdate=September 1, 2016}}</ref> On October 6, 2016, SiR released the EP titled ''HER'' which includes a feature on \"Cadillac Dreams\" from [[Big K.R.I.T.]]. In January 2017, it was announced that SiR signed to [[Top Dawg Entertainment]]. On February 10, 2017, he released his first EP on the label titled ''HER TOO'' with [[Anderson .Paak]] as a guest appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/01/19/tde-announces-sir-signing-john-doe-ws-boi|title=TDE Announces SiR As Latest Signing|website=Thefader.com|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> On January 18, 2018, SiR released his major label debut album ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]''.\n\n===2019\u2014present: ''Chasing Summer''===\nOn August 8, 2019, SiR announced that his second album via TDE, releasing the first single off the album, \"Hair Down\" featuring [[Kendrick Lamar]].<ref name=\"chs\">{{cite web |last1=Strauss |first1=Matthew |title=Kendrick Lamar Joins Top Dawg\u2019s SiR for New Song \u201cHair Down\u201d: Listen |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/kendrick-lamar-joins-top-dawgs-sir-for-new-song-hair-down-listen/ |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |accessdate=August 12, 2019 |date=August 8, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Chasing Summer]]'' was released on August 30, 2019, and includes guest features from [[Kendrick Lamar]], [[Lil Wayne]], [[Jill Scott]], [[Smino]], [[Kadhja Bonet]], [[Sabrina Claudio]], and [[Zacari]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Price |first1=Joe |title=Here's SiR's New Album 'Chasing Summer' f/ Kendrick Lamar, Lil Wayne, Smino, and More |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/08/sir-chasing-summer-stream |website=Complex |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref> \n\nOn April 23, 2020, as part of [[Top Dawg Entertainment]]'s Fan Appreciation Week, SiR released the song ''Rapper Weed'' featuring [[Boogie (rapper)|Boogie]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shifferaw |first1=Abel |title=SiR Drops New Track \"Rapper Weed\" Featuring Boogie |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/sir-rapper-weed-boogie |website=Complex |accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.4em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/billboardcharts/status/1171067165618921472|title=Debuts on this week's #Billboard200 (1/2): #1, @Tool Fear Inoculum #3, @LanaDelRey Norman Fucking Rockwell! #4, @liltecca We Love You Tecca #30, @SherylCrow Threads #34, @StickFigureDub World On Fire #57, @trishayearwood Every Girl #64, @inglewoodSiR Chasing Summer|first=Billboard|last=Charts|website=Twitter.com|date=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Seven Sundays''\n|\n* Released: July 31, 2015\n* Label: Fresh Selects\n* Format: Digital download\n| \u2014\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]''\n|\n* Released: January 19, 2018\n* Label: [[Top Dawg Entertainment|Top Dawg]]\n* Format: Digital download\n| \u2014\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chasing Summer]]''\n|\n* Released: August 30, 2019<ref name=\"chs\"></ref>\n* Label: Top Dawg, [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n| 64\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''HER''\n|\n* Released: October 6, 2016\n* Label: Top Dawg\n* Format: Digital download \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''HER TOO''\n|\n* Released: February 10, 2017\n* Label: Top Dawg\n* Format: Digital download \n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Wooden Voodoo''\n|\n* Released: September 25, 2012\n* Format: Digital download \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Long Live Dilla''\n|\n* Released: February 17, 2014\n* Format: Digital download \n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of non-single guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Already\"\n| 2014\n| [[Anderson .Paak]]\n| ''[[Venice (Anderson Paak album)|Venice]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Ways\"\n| 2015\n| [[Jay Rock]]\n| ''[[90059]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Rope / Rosegold\"\n| 2016\n| [[Isaiah Rashad]]\n| ''[[The Sun's Tirade]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Underwater\"\n| 2017\n| [[EarthGang]]\n| ''[[Robots (EP)|Robots]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Old Age\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| [[Masego (musician)|Masego]]\n| ''[[Lady Lady (album)|Lady Lady]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Make It Out Alive\"\n| [[Nao (singer)|Nao]]\n| ''[[Saturn (album)|Saturn]]''\n|-\n! scope=row | \"Iman\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/artist/3599189|title=Rapsody {{!}} Eve|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref>\n| 2019\n| [[Rapsody]], [[JID]]\n| ''[[Eve (Rapsody album)|Eve]]''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[Category:American soul singers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Inglewood, California]]\n[[Category:RCA Records artists]]\n[[Category:Record producers from California]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Top Dawg Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = SiR\n| image            = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| alias            = \n| birth_name       = Sir Darryl Farris\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1986|11|05}}\n| birth_place      = [[Inglewood, California]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Soul music|soul]]}}\n| instrument       = [[Singing|Vocals]]\n| occupation       = {{hlist|[[Singing|Singer]]|[[songwriter]]|[[record producer]]}}\n| years_active     = 2012\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Top Dawg Entertainment|Top Dawg]]|[[RCA Records|RCA]]|Fresh Selects (former)}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Kendrick Lamar]]|[[Anderson Paak]]|[[Jay Rock]]|[[Isaiah Rashad]]|[[Big K.R.I.T.]]|[[EarthGang]]|[[Schoolboy Q]]}}\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Sir Darryl Farris''' (born November 5, 1986), known mononymously as '''Sir''' (stylized as '''SiR'''), is an American [[Singing|singer]], [[songwriter]] and [[record producer]] from [[Inglewood, California]]. He is signed to [[Top Dawg Entertainment]] and released his debut album on the label titled ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]'' on January 19, 2018. \n\n==Early life==\nSir Darryl Farris grew up in a musical family with his mother, brothers, and cousin being gospel singers in Inglewood. He earned a degree in recording arts at the [[Los Angeles Film School|Los Angeles Film School ]] and developed his songwriting, arranging, and production skills. His mother was a backup singer for [[Michael Jackson]] and [[Anita Baker]], and his uncle [[Andrew Gouche]] was a bassist for [[Prince (musician)|Prince]], and he is the younger brother of rapper [[D Smoke]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/sir-mn0003419699/biography|title=SiR - Biography & History - AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"LAWeekly\">{{cite web |title=R&B SINGER-SONGWRITER SIR IS PROUD TO REP INGLEWOOD'S THRIVING MUSIC SCENE |url=https://www.laweekly.com/rb-singer-songwriter-sir-is-proud-to-rep-inglewoods-thriving-music-scene/ |website=LA Weekly |accessdate=4 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\n===2007\u20142014: Career beginnings===\nIn 2007, SiR joined a songwriting group called WoodWorks with his brothers and his cousin [[Tiffany Gouch\u00e9]], who wrote songs for [[Jaheim]] and [[The Pussycat Dolls]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Interview: Jill Scott, Tyrese and Bilal songwriter SiR |url=https://www.factmag.com/2015/08/02/sir-interview/ |website=Fact Mag |accessdate=4 November 2019}}</ref> He landed a job engineering for [[Tyrese Gibson]] in 2012 while quietly developing his craft as a songwriter. After meeting the songwriting duo [[Dre & Vidal]], he went on to work with [[Anita Baker]] and, from 2011 through 2015, co-wrote material for the likes of [[Ginuwine]], [[Jill Scott]], and [[Stevie Wonder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2017-01-23-sir-signs-to-tde|title=An Introduction to SiR, TDE\u2019s Soulful New Signing|website=Djbooth.net|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> In 2014, he featured on [[Anderson .Paak]]'s album ''[[Venice (Anderson Paak album)|Venice]]''.\n\n===2015\u20142018: Signing to Top Dawg Entertainment and ''November''===\nOn July 31, 2015, SiR released his first independent album titled ''Seven Sundays'', which got the attention of [[Dave Free]]. He was later featured on [[Jay Rock]]'s ''[[90059]]'' on the song \"The Ways\", and [[Isaiah Rashad]]'s ''[[The Sun's Tirade]]'' on the song \"Rope / Rosegold\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Yoh|title=TDE Reveals Lance SkiiiWalker is Their \"John Doe\" New Artist - DJBooth Article|url=http://djbooth.net/news/entry/2016-05-11-lance-skiiiwalker-tde-new-artist|website=DJBooth.net|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2016/08/30/isaiah-rashad-the-suns-tirade-tracklisting/ |title=Isaiah Rashad Taps Kendrick Lamar, Jay Rock for 'The Sun's Tirade' |work=[[Rap-Up]] |date=August 30, 2016 |accessdate=September 1, 2016}}</ref> On October 6, 2016, SiR released the EP titled ''HER'' which includes a feature on \"Cadillac Dreams\" from [[Big K.R.I.T.]]. In January 2017, it was announced that SiR signed to [[Top Dawg Entertainment]]. On February 10, 2017, he released his first EP on the label titled ''HER TOO'' with [[Anderson .Paak]] as a guest appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/01/19/tde-announces-sir-signing-john-doe-ws-boi|title=TDE Announces SiR As Latest Signing|website=Thefader.com|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> On January 18, 2018, SiR released his major label debut album ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]''.\n\n===2019\u2014present: ''Chasing Summer''===\nOn August 8, 2019, SiR announced that his second album via TDE, releasing the first single off the album, \"Hair Down\" featuring [[Kendrick Lamar]].<ref name=\"chs\">{{cite web |last1=Strauss |first1=Matthew |title=Kendrick Lamar Joins Top Dawg\u2019s SiR for New Song \u201cHair Down\u201d: Listen |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/kendrick-lamar-joins-top-dawgs-sir-for-new-song-hair-down-listen/ |website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |accessdate=August 12, 2019 |date=August 8, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Chasing Summer]]'' was released on August 30, 2019, and includes guest features from [[Kendrick Lamar]], [[Lil Wayne]], [[Jill Scott]], [[Smino]], [[Kadhja Bonet]], [[Sabrina Claudio]], and [[Zacari]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Price |first1=Joe |title=Here's SiR's New Album 'Chasing Summer' f/ Kendrick Lamar, Lil Wayne, Smino, and More |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/08/sir-chasing-summer-stream |website=Complex |accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.4em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/billboardcharts/status/1171067165618921472|title=Debuts on this week's #Billboard200 (1/2): #1, @Tool Fear Inoculum #3, @LanaDelRey Norman Fucking Rockwell! #4, @liltecca We Love You Tecca #30, @SherylCrow Threads #34, @StickFigureDub World On Fire #57, @trishayearwood Every Girl #64, @inglewoodSiR Chasing Summer|first=Billboard|last=Charts|website=Twitter.com|date=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Seven Sundays''\n|\n* Released: July 31, 2015\n* Label: Fresh Selects\n* Format: Digital download\n| \u2014\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[November (Sir album)|November]]''\n|\n* Released: January 19, 2018\n* Label: [[Top Dawg Entertainment|Top Dawg]]\n* Format: Digital download\n| \u2014\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Chasing Summer]]''\n|\n* Released: August 30, 2019<ref name=\"chs\"></ref>\n* Label: Top Dawg, [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n| 64\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''HER''\n|\n* Released: October 6, 2016\n* Label: Top Dawg\n* Format: Digital download \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''HER TOO''\n|\n* Released: February 10, 2017\n* Label: Top Dawg\n* Format: Digital download \n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Wooden Voodoo''\n|\n* Released: September 25, 2012\n* Format: Digital download \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Long Live Dilla''\n|\n* Released: February 17, 2014\n* Format: Digital download \n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of non-single guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Already\"\n| 2014\n| [[Anderson .Paak]]\n| ''[[Venice (Anderson Paak album)|Venice]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Ways\"\n| 2015\n| [[Jay Rock]]\n| ''[[90059]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Rope / Rosegold\"\n| 2016\n| [[Isaiah Rashad]]\n| ''[[The Sun's Tirade]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Underwater\"\n| 2017\n| [[EarthGang]]\n| ''[[Robots (EP)|Robots]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Old Age\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| [[Masego (musician)|Masego]]\n| ''[[Lady Lady (album)|Lady Lady]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Make It Out Alive\"\n| [[Nao (singer)|Nao]]\n| ''[[Saturn (album)|Saturn]]''\n|-\n! scope=row | \"Iman\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/artist/3599189|title=Rapsody {{!}} Eve|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref>\n| 2019\n| [[Rapsody]], [[JID]]\n| ''[[Eve (Rapsody album)|Eve]]''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[Category:American soul singers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Inglewood, California]]\n[[Category:RCA Records artists]]\n[[Category:Record producers from California]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Top Dawg Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n", "name_user": "Kaisquared", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2019\u2014present: Chasing Summer", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sir_(singer)"}
{"title_page": "Lucas Mendes (footballer, born 1992)", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Lucas Mendes\n| fullname            = Lucas Ferreira Mendes da Silva\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1992|02|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Guariba]], [[Brazil]]\n| height              = 1.74 m\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Right-back]]\n| currentclub         = [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         = 2008\u20132012\n| youthclubs1         = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| years1              = 2011\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\t| caps1 = 0{{efn|Soccerway shows one appearance in [[2011 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]], but there is no evidence of this when clicking through.}} | goals1  =  0\n| years2              = 2012 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9|Santo Andr\u00e9]] (loan) | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0\n| years3              = 2014 | clubs3 = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro)|Inter de Bebedouro]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 2015 | clubs4 = [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] | caps4 = 0 | goals4 = 0\n| years5              = 2015 | clubs5 = [[Uberaba Sport Club|Uberaba]] | caps5 = 0 | goals5 = 0\n| years6              = 2016 | clubs6 = [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] | caps6 = 14 | goals6 = 0\n| years7              = 2016 | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] (loan) | caps7 = 9 | goals7 = 0\n| years8              = 2017 | clubs8 = [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] | caps8 = 9 | goals8 = 0\n| years9              = 2018 | clubs9 = [[Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube|Sert\u00e3ozinho]] | caps9 = 11 | goals9 = 0\n| years10             = 2018\u20132019 | clubs10 = [[Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP)|Botafogo-SP]] | caps10 = 41 | goals10 = 0\n| years11             = 2020\u2013 | clubs11 = [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]] | caps11 = 11 | goals11 = 0\n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| club-update         = 10:04, 21 June 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n{{noteslist}}\n}}\n\n'''Lucas Ferreira Mendes da Silva''', commonly known as '''Lucas Mendes''', is a Brazilian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|right-back]] for [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]].\n\n==Career==\nLucas Mendes came through the youth ranks with [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]. After performing well in the 2011 [[Copa S\u00e3o Paulo de Futebol J\u00fanior]] he was loaned to  [[Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9|Santo Andr\u00e9]] in 2012 for their second division [[Campeonato Paulista]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2012/02/13/sao-paulo-empresta-lucas-mendes-e-sergio-mota-para-o-santo-andre.htm?action=print|title=S\u00e3o Paulo empresta Lucas Mendes e S\u00e9rgio Mota para o Santo Andr\u00e9|publisher=UOL|language=pt|date=13 February 2012}}</ref> Between 2014 and 2016 he represented [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro)|Inter de Bebedouro]], [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] and [[Uberaba Sport Club|Uberaba]] in the lower divisions of Campeonato Paulista and [[Campeonato Mineiro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.odiarioonline.com.br/noticia/32144/BEC-ANUNCIA-CONTRATACAO-DO-LATERAL-DIREITO-LUCAS-MENDES|title=BEC anuncia contrata\u00e7\u00e3o do lateral direito Lucas Mendes|publisher=O Di\u00e1rio|language=pt|date=3 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/triangulo-mineiro/noticia/2015/08/usc-anuncia-lateral-direito-formado-no-sao-paulo-para-sequencia-do-mineiro.html|title=USC anuncia lateral-direito formado no S\u00e3o Paulo para sequ\u00eancia do Mineiro|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=21 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futebolbarretos.com.br/principal.php?xidalt=5696&xvar=ver_noticia|title=18/11/2015 - Lateral Lucas Mendes pode voltar a defender o BEC na A2!|publisher=futebolbarettos.com.br|language=pt|date=18 November 2015}}</ref> He was loaned by Barretos to [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] in May 2016 to play in [[2016 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jornaldebarretos.com.br/esportes/lucas-mendes-acerta-com-sao-bento/|title=Lucas Mendes acerta com S\u00e3o Bento|publisher=Jornal de Barretos|language=pt|date=19 May 2016}}</ref> S\u00e3o Bento won promotion, and he stayed with them for the whole of 2017, winning promotion again from [[2017 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C]].<ref name=taubate>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebolinterior.com.br/futebol/Taubate-SP/noticias/2017-11/com-acessos-pelo-sao-bento-lucas-mendes-acerta-com-taubate|title=Paulista A2: Ex-S\u00e3o Paulo and with accesses by S\u00e3o Bento, lateral hits Taubat\u00e9|publisher=Futebol Interior|language=pt|date=28 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017 it was announce that Lucas Mendes had signed for [[Esporte Clube Taubat\u00e9|Taubat\u00e9]] to compete in the 2018 Campeonato Paulista second division, but by the time the season started in January he had moved to rivals [[Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube|Sert\u00e3ozinho]].<ref name=taubate /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sertaozinhofc.com.br/fora-de-casa-e-com-um-a-menos-sertaozinho-vence-a-primeira-na-serie-a2/|title=Fora de casa e com um a menos, Sert\u00e3ozinho vence a primeira na S\u00e9rie A2|publisher=Sert\u00e3ozinho FC Official Site|language=pt|date=24 January 2018}}</ref> In April 2018 he signed for [[Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP)|Botafogo-SP]] to compete in [[2018 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acidadeon.com/ribeiraopreto/esportes/NOT,0,0,1318949,tricolor+de+ribeirao+preto+confirma+mais+dois+reforcos.aspx|title=Tricolor de Ribeir\u00e3o Preto confirma mais dois refor\u00e7os|publisher=ACidadeON|language=pt|date=5 April 2018}}</ref> After gaining promotion at the end of the season, he renewed his contract with Botafogo-SP for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/ribeirao-preto-e-regiao/futebol/times/botafogo-sp/noticia/lucas-mendes-renova-e-e-segundo-reforco-do-botafogo-sp-para-2019.ghtml|title=Lucas Mendes renova e \u00e9 segundo refor\u00e7o do Botafogo-SP para 2019|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=27 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|191102}}\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|184632<!-- --lucas_mendes -->}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mendes, Lucas}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:S\u00e3o Paulo FC players]]\n[[Category:Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9 players]]\n[[Category:Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro) players]]\n[[Category:Barretos Esporte Clube players]]\n[[Category:Uberaba Sport Club players]]\n[[Category:Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento players]]\n[[Category:Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube players]]\n[[Category:Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP) players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie B players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Lucas Mendes\n| fullname            = Lucas Ferreira Mendes da Silva\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1992|02|19}}\n| birth_place         = [[Guariba]], [[Brazil]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)|Right-back]]\n| currentclub         = [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         = 2008\u20132012\n| youthclubs1         = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| years1              = 2011\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\t| caps1 = 0{{efn|Soccerway shows one appearance in [[2011 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]], but there is no evidence of this when clicking through.}} | goals1  =  0\n| years2              = 2012 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9|Santo Andr\u00e9]] (loan) | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0\n| years3              = 2014 | clubs3 = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro)|Inter de Bebedouro]] | caps3 = 0 | goals3 = 0 \n| years4              = 2015 | clubs4 = [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] | caps4 = 0 | goals4 = 0\n| years5              = 2015 | clubs5 = [[Uberaba Sport Club|Uberaba]] | caps5 = 0 | goals5 = 0\n| years6              = 2016 | clubs6 = [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] | caps6 = 14 | goals6 = 0\n| years7              = 2016 | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] (loan) | caps7 = 9 | goals7 = 0\n| years8              = 2017 | clubs8 = [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] | caps8 = 9 | goals8 = 0\n| years9              = 2018 | clubs9 = [[Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube|Sert\u00e3ozinho]] | caps9 = 11 | goals9 = 0\n| years10             = 2018\u20132019 | clubs10 = [[Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP)|Botafogo-SP]] | caps10 = 41 | goals10 = 0\n| years11             = 2020\u2013 | clubs11 = [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]] | caps11 = 11 | goals11 = 0\n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| club-update         = 10:04, 21 June 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update =\n{{noteslist}}\n}}\n\n'''Lucas Ferreira Mendes da Silva''', commonly known as '''Lucas Mendes''', is a Brazilian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|right-back]] for [[Clube de Regatas Brasil|CRB]].\n\n==Career==\nLucas Mendes came through the youth ranks with [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]. After performing well in the 2011 [[Copa S\u00e3o Paulo de Futebol J\u00fanior]] he was loaned to  [[Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9|Santo Andr\u00e9]] in 2012 for their second division [[Campeonato Paulista]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2012/02/13/sao-paulo-empresta-lucas-mendes-e-sergio-mota-para-o-santo-andre.htm?action=print|title=S\u00e3o Paulo empresta Lucas Mendes e S\u00e9rgio Mota para o Santo Andr\u00e9|publisher=UOL|language=pt|date=13 February 2012}}</ref> Between 2014 and 2016 he represented [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro)|Inter de Bebedouro]], [[Barretos Esporte Clube|Barretos]] and [[Uberaba Sport Club|Uberaba]] in the lower divisions of Campeonato Paulista and [[Campeonato Mineiro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.odiarioonline.com.br/noticia/32144/BEC-ANUNCIA-CONTRATACAO-DO-LATERAL-DIREITO-LUCAS-MENDES|title=BEC anuncia contrata\u00e7\u00e3o do lateral direito Lucas Mendes|publisher=O Di\u00e1rio|language=pt|date=3 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/triangulo-mineiro/noticia/2015/08/usc-anuncia-lateral-direito-formado-no-sao-paulo-para-sequencia-do-mineiro.html|title=USC anuncia lateral-direito formado no S\u00e3o Paulo para sequ\u00eancia do Mineiro|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=21 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.futebolbarretos.com.br/principal.php?xidalt=5696&xvar=ver_noticia|title=18/11/2015 - Lateral Lucas Mendes pode voltar a defender o BEC na A2!|publisher=futebolbarettos.com.br|language=pt|date=18 November 2015}}</ref> He was loaned by Barretos to [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]] in May 2016 to play in [[2016 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jornaldebarretos.com.br/esportes/lucas-mendes-acerta-com-sao-bento/|title=Lucas Mendes acerta com S\u00e3o Bento|publisher=Jornal de Barretos|language=pt|date=19 May 2016}}</ref> S\u00e3o Bento won promotion, and he stayed with them for the whole of 2017, winning promotion again from [[2017 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C]].<ref name=taubate>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebolinterior.com.br/futebol/Taubate-SP/noticias/2017-11/com-acessos-pelo-sao-bento-lucas-mendes-acerta-com-taubate|title=Paulista A2: Ex-S\u00e3o Paulo and with accesses by S\u00e3o Bento, lateral hits Taubat\u00e9|publisher=Futebol Interior|language=pt|date=28 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017 it was announce that Lucas Mendes had signed for [[Esporte Clube Taubat\u00e9|Taubat\u00e9]] to compete in the 2018 Campeonato Paulista second division, but by the time the season started in January he had moved to rivals [[Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube|Sert\u00e3ozinho]].<ref name=taubate /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sertaozinhofc.com.br/fora-de-casa-e-com-um-a-menos-sertaozinho-vence-a-primeira-na-serie-a2/|title=Fora de casa e com um a menos, Sert\u00e3ozinho vence a primeira na S\u00e9rie A2|publisher=Sert\u00e3ozinho FC Official Site|language=pt|date=24 January 2018}}</ref> In April 2018 he signed for [[Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP)|Botafogo-SP]] to compete in [[2018 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acidadeon.com/ribeiraopreto/esportes/NOT,0,0,1318949,tricolor+de+ribeirao+preto+confirma+mais+dois+reforcos.aspx|title=Tricolor de Ribeir\u00e3o Preto confirma mais dois refor\u00e7os|publisher=ACidadeON|language=pt|date=5 April 2018}}</ref> After gaining promotion at the end of the season, he renewed his contract with Botafogo-SP for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/ribeirao-preto-e-regiao/futebol/times/botafogo-sp/noticia/lucas-mendes-renova-e-e-segundo-reforco-do-botafogo-sp-para-2019.ghtml|title=Lucas Mendes renova e \u00e9 segundo refor\u00e7o do Botafogo-SP para 2019|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=27 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|191102}}\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|184632--lucas_mendes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mendes, Lucas}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:S\u00e3o Paulo FC players]]\n[[Category:Esporte Clube Santo Andr\u00e9 players]]\n[[Category:Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Atl\u00e9tica Internacional (Bebedouro) players]]\n[[Category:Barretos Esporte Clube players]]\n[[Category:Uberaba Sport Club players]]\n[[Category:Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento players]]\n[[Category:Sert\u00e3ozinho Futebol Clube players]]\n[[Category:Botafogo Futebol Clube (SP) players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie B players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie C players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D players]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update FootballDatabase.eu template, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucas_Mendes_(footballer,_born_1992)"}
{"title_page": "Hans Schack, 2nd Count of Schackenborg", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish nobleman}}\n{{Infobox noble|type\n| name              = Hans Schack\n| title             = [[Count of Schackenborg]]\n| image             = \n| caption           = \n| alt               = \n| CoA               = \n| more              = no \n| succession        = [[Count of Schackenborg]]\n| reign             = 1 July 1683 \u2013 22 September 1719\n| reign-type        = Tenure\n| predecessor       = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]\n| successor         = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]\n| suc-type          = \n| spouse            = Anna Margrethe Reventlow <br/> [[Anna Sophie Rantzau]]\n| spouse-type       = \n| issue             = {{Blist|Frederik August Schack|Louise Schack|Conrad Schack|[[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg]]|Anna Margrethe Schack}}\n| issue-link        = Hans Schack, 2nd Count of Schackenborg#Family\n| issue-pipe        = Detail\n| full name         = Hans Schack\n| native_name       = \n| styles            = \n| titles            = \n| noble family      = [[Schack (noble family)|Schack]]\n| house-type        = \n| father            = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg]]\n| mother            = Sophie Dorothea von Marschalk\n| birth_name        =\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date|1676|03|04|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Ribe]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| christening_date  = \n| christening_place = \n| death_date        = {{Death date and age|1719|09|22|1676|03|04|df=y}}\n| death_place       = [[Copenhagen]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| burial_date       = \n| burial_place      = [[M\u00f8gelt\u00f8nder Church]], [[M\u00f8gelt\u00f8nder]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| religion          = [[Lutheran]]\n| occupation        = \n| memorials         = \n| module            = \n}}\n'''Hans Schack, Count of Schackenborg''' (4 March 1676 \u2013 22 September 1719) was a Danish [[nobleman]] and [[lensgreve|enfeoffed count]] ({{lang-da|lensgreve}}). He was the second holder of the [[County of Schackenborg]] from 1683 to 1719.\n\n== Biography ==\nHans Schack was born on 4 March 1676 in [[Ribe]] in the [[Kingdom of Denmark]]. Born into the [[noble family]] of [[Schack (noble family)|Schack]], he was the second child and eldest surviving son of the Danish [[nobleman]] and [[civil servant]] [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]], and his second wife Sophie Dorothea von Marschalk.<ref name=\"DAA1932\">[https://dis-danmark.dk/bibliotek/911059.pdf Danmarks Adels Aarbog, 1932], p. 63.</ref>\n\nAt the death of his grandfather in February 1676, his father had inherited the large [[manor]]s of [[Schackenborg]] and [[Gram Castle|Gram]] in [[Southern Jutland]], and [[Gisselfeld]] in [[Zealand]]. Later in the same year, on 23 June 1676, Otto Didrik Schack was awarded the [[title]] of [[enfeoffed count]] ({{lang-da|lensgreve}}), as the [[County of Schackenborg]] was created from the manors of [[Schackenborg]], [[S\u00f8damg\u00e5rd]], [[Solvig]], and [[Store T\u00f8nde]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n\nAt the death of his father on 1 July 1683, he inherited the [[County of Schackenborg]] and assumed the title of enfeoffed count.<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> From 1692 he was educated at the [[knight academy]] in [[Copenhagen]] that prepared aristocratic youth for state and military service, and in 1695, he was made a [[chamberlain (office)|chamberlain]] at the Danish court. On 19 October 1697, he was appointed [[amtmann]] of the [[Amt (country subdivision)|Amt]] of [[Riberhus Amt|Riberhus]], and on 15 August the following year, he was awarded the [[Order of the Dannebrog]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> \n\nIn 1702, he entered into French military service. As such he participated in the [[Battle of Blenheim]] in 1704 during the [[War of the Spanish Succession]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> On 22 July 1712, he was made a [[Geheimrat]] in the [[privy council]]. On 26 October 1716 he was awarded the [[Order of the Elephant]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> \n\nCount Schack died already on 22 September 1719, aged only 43, in [[Copenhagen]] in the [[Kingdom of Denmark]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> He was succeeded by his eldest surviving son, [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]].\n\n==Family==\nSchack married firstly on 16 March 1699 in the chapel of [[Christiansborg Palace]] Countess Anne Margrethe Reventlow, daughter of [[Grand Chancellor of Denmark|Grand Chancellor]] Count [[Conrad von Reventlow]] and Sophie Amalie von Hahn, by whom he had four children. She died on 21 March 1710.<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n* Count Frederik August Schack (1707\u20131707)\n* Baroness Louise Schack (1707\u20131707)\n* Count Conrad Schack (1708\u20131709)\n* [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]], who succeeded him as 3rd Count of Schackenborg.\n\nSchack married secondly in 1711 in [[Hamburg]] [[Anna Sophie Rantzau]], daughter of [[Christian von Rantzau]] and Margrethe Rantzau, by whom he had one child:<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n* Baroness Anne Margrethe Schack (1713\u20131720)\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Danmarks Adels Aarbog 1932|url=https://dis-danmark.dk/bibliotek/911059.pdf |location=[[Copenhagen]] |publisher=J.H. Schultz |year=1932 |page= |date= |isbn=}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{in lang|da}} [https://schackenborg.dk/ Official website of Schackenborg Castle]\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|dk}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title=[[Count of Schackenborg]] | years=1683\u20131719}}\n{{s-aft | after=[[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Schack, Hans, 2nd Count Of Schackenborg}}\n[[Category:1676 births]]\n[[Category:1719 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century Danish people]]\n[[Category:18th-century Danish people]]\n[[Category:Danish nobility]]\n[[Category:People from Esbjerg Municipality]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Order of the Dannebrog]]\n[[Category:Counts of Denmark]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Danish nobleman}}\n{{Infobox noble|type\n| name              = Hans Schack\n| title             = [[Count of Schackenborg]]\n| image             = \n| caption           = \n| alt               = \n| CoA               = \n| more              = no \n| succession        = [[Count of Schackenborg]]\n| reign             = 1 July 1683 \u2013 22 September 1719\n| reign-type        = Tenure\n| predecessor       = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]\n| successor         = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]\n| suc-type          = \n| spouse            = Anna Margrethe Reventlow <br/> [[Anna Sophie Rantzau]]\n| spouse-type       = \n| issue             = {{Blist|Frederik August Schack|Louise Schack|Conrad Schack|[[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg]]|Anna Margrethe Schack}}\n| issue-link        = Hans Schack, 2nd Count of Schackenborg#Family\n| issue-pipe        = Detail\n| full name         = Hans Schack\n| native_name       = \n| styles            = \n| titles            = \n| noble family      = [[Schack (noble family)|Schack]]\n| house-type        = \n| father            = [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg]]\n| mother            = Sophie Dorothea von Marschalk\n| birth_name        =\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date|1676|03|04|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Ribe]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| christening_date  = \n| christening_place = \n| death_date        = {{Death date and age|1719|09|22|1676|03|04|df=y}}\n| death_place       = [[Copenhagen]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| burial_date       = \n| burial_place      = [[M\u00f8gelt\u00f8nder Church]], [[M\u00f8gelt\u00f8nder]], [[Kingdom of Denmark]]\n| religion          = [[Lutheran]]\n| occupation        = \n| memorials         = \n| module            = \n}}\n'''Hans Schack, Count of Schackenborg''' (4 March 1676 \u2013 22 September 1719) was a Danish [[nobleman]] and [[lensgreve|enfeoffed count]] ({{lang-da|lensgreve}}). He was the second holder of the [[County of Schackenborg]] from 1683 to 1719.\n\n== Biography ==\nHans Schack was born on 4 March 1676 in [[Ribe]] in the [[Kingdom of Denmark]]. Born into the [[noble family]] of [[Schack (noble family)|Schack]], he was the second child and eldest surviving son of the Danish [[nobleman]] and [[civil servant]] [[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]], and his second wife Sophie Dorothea von Marschalk.<ref name=\"DAA1932\">[https://dis-danmark.dk/bibliotek/911059.pdf Danmarks Adels Aarbog, 1932], p. 63.</ref>\n\nAt the death of his grandfather in February 1676, his father had inherited the large [[manor]]s of [[Schackenborg]] and [[Gram Castle|Gram]] in [[Southern Jutland]], and [[Gisselfeld]] in [[Zealand]]. Later in the same year, on 23 June 1676, Otto Didrik Schack was awarded the [[title]] of [[enfeoffed count]] ({{lang-da|lensgreve}}), as the [[County of Schackenborg]] was created from the manors of [[Schackenborg]], [[S\u00f8damg\u00e5rd]], [[Solvig]], and [[Store T\u00f8nde]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n\nAt the death of his father on 1 July 1683, he inherited the [[County of Schackenborg]] and assumed the title of enfeoffed count.<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> From 1692 he was educated at the [[knight academy]] in [[Copenhagen]] that prepared aristocratic youth for state and military service, and in 1695, he was made a [[chamberlain (office)|chamberlain]] at the Danish court. On 19 October 1697, he was appointed [[amtmann]] of the [[Amt (country subdivision)|Amt]] of [[Riberhus Amt|Riberhus]], and on 15 August the following year, he was awarded the [[Order of the Dannebrog]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> \n\nIn 1702, he entered into French military service. As such he participated in the [[Battle of Blenheim]] in 1704 during the [[War of the Spanish Succession]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> On 22 July 1712, he was made a [[Geheimrat]] in the [[privy council]]. On 26 October 1716 he was awarded the [[Order of the Elephant]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> \n\nCount Schack died already on 22 September 1719, aged only 43, in [[Copenhagen]] in the [[Kingdom of Denmark]].<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/> He was succeeded by his eldest surviving son, [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]].\n\n==Family==\nSchack married firstly on 16 March 1699 in the chapel of [[Christiansborg Palace]] Countess Anne Margrethe Reventlow, daughter of [[Grand Chancellor of Denmark|Grand Chancellor]] Count [[Conrad von Reventlow]] and Sophie Amalie von Hahn, by whom he had four children. She died on 21 March 1710.<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n* Count Frederik August Schack (1707\u20131707)\n* Baroness Louise Schack (1707\u20131707)\n* Count Conrad Schack (1708\u20131709)\n* [[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]], who succeeded him as 3rd Count of Schackenborg.\n\nSchack married secondly in 1711 in [[Hamburg]] [[Anna Sophie Rantzau]], daughter of [[Christian von Rantzau]] and Margrethe Rantzau, by whom he had one child:<ref name=\"DAA1932\"/>\n* Baroness Anne Margrethe Schack (1713\u20131720)\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n*{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Danmarks Adels Aarbog 1932|url=https://dis-danmark.dk/bibliotek/911059.pdf |location=[[Copenhagen]] |publisher=J.H. Schultz |year=1932 |page= |date= |isbn=}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{in lang|da}} [https://schackenborg.dk/ Official website of Schackenborg Castle]\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-reg|dk}}\n{{s-bef | before=[[Otto Didrik Schack, 1st Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title=[[Count of Schackenborg]] | years=1683\u20131719}}\n{{s-aft | after=[[Otto Didrik Schack, 3rd Count of Schackenborg|Otto Didrik Schack]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Schack, Hans, 2nd Count Of Schackenborg}}\n[[Category:1676 births]]\n[[Category:1719 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century Danish people]]\n[[Category:18th-century Danish people]]\n[[Category:Danish nobility]]\n[[Category:People from T\u00f8nder Municipality]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Order of the Dannebrog]]\n[[Category:Counts of Denmark]]\n", "name_user": "ArbieP", "label": "safe", "comment": "amended toCategory:People from Esbjerg Municipality", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Schack,_2nd_Count_of_Schackenborg"}
